cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.LG

The paper deals with privacy issues related to location-based services and proposes a solution based on differential privacy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses real mobility traces and discusses the overhead incurred on mobile devices, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper deals with semantic precision and quasi-identifiers, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical guarantees of Geo-Indistinguishability, which could also place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
